# Routing Structure

- All routing logic must be placed inside `src/app/router/`.
- Do not define routes inside `App.tsx` or inside page components.
- Use a dedicated `routes.ts` file for route configuration.
- Use `index.tsx` for router setup and router provider wiring.
- Use lazy loading for route components via `React.lazy`.
- Wrap lazy-loaded routes with `Suspense` and provide a clear loading fallback.
- Keep one route object per page/feature and compose routes in `routes.ts`.
- Prefer route-level code splitting to reduce initial bundle size.
- Handle unknown routes with a dedicated `NotFound` route.

## Expected Router Files

```text
src/app/router/
  index.tsx
  routes.ts
```
